# Wellfit QA — Azure App Service menu map (STAGE)

Chris has Azure portal access. When guiding him, **name the exact left-nav item** from the App Service blade — do not invent alternate paths.

## Target apps (STAGE)

| App | Typical use |
|-----|-------------|
| `stage-wf-worldpay-wrapper-api` | PAY-4032 Part A eCheck/redeposit, Vantiv Pre-Live |
| `stage-wf-payment-management-api` | PM flags (e.g. AchRetry), PM API |
| `stage-wf-identity-api` | Identity token host |

Resource group is often under **stage-platform-api** (confirm in Overview).

## Left-nav map (App Service blade)

Chris sees sections like this (names may vary slightly by portal version):

### Settings (config / secrets)

| Click | What for |
|-------|----------|
| **Environment variables** | App settings + connection strings (preferred for `processor__vantiv__*`, feature flags) |
| **Configuration** | Older/alternate blade for same app settings — use if Environment variables missing |
| **Identity** | Managed identity |
| **Authentication** | Easy Auth (usually N/A for these APIs) |

**Do not ask Chris to change Key Vault–backed secrets** unless he owns that change. Prefer Show value / read-only.

### Monitoring (logs)

| Click | What for |
|-------|----------|
| **Application Insights** | Opens App Insights link for this app — **first stop for request/txn investigation** |
| **Logs** | App Service / diagnostic log queries (secondary) |
| **Log stream** | Live stdout (noisy; only for live Send debugging) |
| **App Service logs** | Enable filesystem/blob logging |
| **Metrics** / **Alerts** | Perf / alert rules — not first for functional 330 |

### After clicking Application Insights

Linked resource for STAGE wrapper: **`stage-insights`** (RG `stage-platform-core`). Overview charts = correct place.

Inside **`stage-insights`** left nav:

| Click | Use |
|-------|-----|
| **Investigate → Failures** | HTTP 5xx / exceptions (may miss business declines that return HTTP 200) |
| **Investigate → Performance** | Slow ops |
| **Monitoring → Logs** | **Best for searching a `transactionId` or `330`** (Kusto) |
| **Transaction search** | If present under Investigate — paste txn id in search box |

For PAY-4032 eCheck `330` (HTTP 200 Declined), prefer **Logs** over Failures.

### Not for this investigation

Deployment Center, Scale, SSH, API Management, Certificates, Networking — skip unless the issue is deploy/hosting.

## STAGE Worldpay Wrapper settings Chris already verified

App: `stage-wf-worldpay-wrapper-api` → **Environment variables**

| Key | Known STAGE value / note |
|-----|--------------------------|
| `wellfit__featureFlags__WorldpayWrapper__ECheckEnabled` | `true` |
| `processor__vantiv__merchantId` | `01264096` (= Postman `accountId`) |
| `processor__vantiv__masterSubMerchantId` | `01291508` (not Postman `subMerchantId`) |
| `processor__vantiv__url` | `https://payments.vantivprelive.com/vap/communicator/online` (Pre-Live — correct) |
| `processor__vantiv__username` / `password` | Key Vault — confirm present; do not paste in chat |

## Guidance style

- One Azure click at a time when walking Chris.
- Quote menu labels **exactly** as in this map (`Application Insights` under **Monitoring**, not “go to logs somewhere”).
- If portal UI differs, ask what he sees under **Monitoring** and match to the closest row above.
